  "root_text": {
    "an3.85:0.1": "Aṅguttara Nikāya 3.85 ",
    "an3.85:0.2": "9. Samaṇavagga ",
    "an3.85:0.3": "Sekkhasutta ",
    "an3.85:1.1": "Atha kho aññataro bhikkhu yena bhagavā tenupasaṅkami; upasaṅkamitvā bhagavantaṁ abhivādetvā ekamantaṁ nisīdi. Ekamantaṁ nisinno kho so bhikkhu bhagavantaṁ etadavoca: ",
    "an3.85:2.1": "“‘Sekho, sekho’ti, bhante, vuccati. ",
    "an3.85:2.2": "Kittāvatā nu kho, bhante, sekho hotī”ti? ",
    "an3.85:2.3": "“Sikkhatīti kho, bhikkhu, tasmā sekhoti vuccati. ",
    "an3.85:2.4": "Kiñca sikkhati? ",
    "an3.85:2.5": "Adhisīlampi sikkhati, adhicittampi sikkhati, adhipaññampi sikkhati. ",
    "an3.85:2.6": "Sikkhatīti kho, bhikkhu, tasmā sekhoti vuccatīti. ",
    "an3.85:3.1": "Sekhassa sikkhamānassa, ",
    "an3.85:3.2": "ujumaggānusārino; ",
    "an3.85:3.3": "Khayasmiṁ paṭhamaṁ ñāṇaṁ, ",
    "an3.85:3.4": "tato aññā anantarā. ",
    "an3.85:4.1": "Tato aññāvimuttassa, ",
    "an3.85:4.2": "ñāṇaṁ ve hoti tādino; ",
    "an3.85:4.3": "Akuppā me vimuttīti, ",
    "an3.85:4.4": "bhavasaṁyojanakkhaye”ti. ",
    "an3.85:4.5": "Pañcamaṁ. "
  },
  "translation_text": {
    "an3.85:0.1": "Numbered Discourses 3.85 ",
    "an3.85:0.2": "9. Ascetics ",
    "an3.85:0.3": "A Trainee ",
    "an3.85:1.1": "Then a mendicant went up to the Buddha, bowed, sat down to one side, and said to him: ",
    "an3.85:2.1": "“Sir, they speak of the one called ‘a trainee’. ",
    "an3.85:2.2": "How is a trainee defined?” ",
    "an3.85:2.3": "“They train, mendicant, that’s why they’re called ‘a trainee’. ",
    "an3.85:2.4": "What is their training? ",
    "an3.85:2.5": "They train in the higher ethics, the higher mind, and the higher wisdom. ",
    "an3.85:2.6": "They train, that’s why they’re called ‘a trainee’. ",
    "an3.85:3.1": "As a trainee trains, ",
    "an3.85:3.2": "following the straight road, ",
    "an3.85:3.3": "first they know about ending; ",
    "an3.85:3.4": "enlightenment follows in the same lifetime. ",
    "an3.85:4.1": "Then the knowledge comes ",
    "an3.85:4.2": "such a one, freed through enlightenment, ",
    "an3.85:4.3": "with the end of the fetters of continued existence: ",
    "an3.85:4.4": "‘My freedom is unshakable.’” "
  },
  "variant_text": {
    "an3.85:4.1": "aññāvimuttassa → aññāvimuttiyā (mr) ",
    "an3.85:4.2": "ñāṇaṁ ve → ñāṇañca (mr) "
  },
